                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " along which to\ncompute the vector norms.  If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "axis"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is a 2-tuple, it specifies the\naxes that hold 2-D matrices, and the matrix norms of these matrices\nare computed.  If "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "axis"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is None then either a vector norm (when "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "x"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": "\nis 1-D) or a matrix norm (when "
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "code",
                        "text": "x"
                      },
                      {
                        "kind": "text",
                        "text": " is 2-D) is returned. The default\nis None."
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ],
                "data_type": "{None, int, 2-tuple of ints}, optional.",
