        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For values of "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ord < 1"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", the result is, strictly speaking, not a\nmathematical 'norm', but it may still be useful for various numerical\npurposes."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The following norms can be calculated:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "table",
            "raw_text": "\n\n\n\n\n\nord\n\nnorm for matrices\n\nnorm for vectors\n\nNone\n\nFrobenius norm\n\n2-norm\n\n'fro'\n\nFrobenius norm\n\n<string>:12: (INFO/1) Unexpected possible title overline or transition.\nTreating it as ordinary text because it's so short.\n\n--\n\n'nuc'\n\nnuclear norm\n\n<string>:13: (INFO/1) Unexpected possible title overline or transition.\nTreating it as ordinary text because it's so short.\n\n--\n\ninf\n\nmax(sum(abs(x), axis=1))\n\nmax(abs(x))\n\n-inf\n\nmin(sum(abs(x), axis=1))\n\nmin(abs(x))\n\n0\n\n<string>:16: (INFO/1) Unexpected possible title overline or transition.\nTreating it as ordinary text because it's so short.\n\n--\n\nsum(x != 0)\n\n1\n\nmax(sum(abs(x), axis=0))\n\nas below\n\n-1\n\nmin(sum(abs(x), axis=0))\n\nas below\n\n2\n\n2-norm (largest sing. value)\n\nas below\n\n-2\n\nsmallest singular value\n\nas below\n\nother\n\n<string>:21: (INFO/1) Unexpected possible title overline or transition.\nTreating it as ordinary text because it's so short.\n\n--\n\nsum(abs(x)**ord)**(1./ord)",
            "type": "raw_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The Frobenius norm is given by "
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "[1]_"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ":"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "||A||_F = [\\sum_{i,j} abs(a_{i,j})^2]^{1/2}"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The nuclear norm is the sum of the singular values."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Both the Frobenius and nuclear norm orders are only defined for\nmatrices and raise a ValueError when "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "x.ndim != 2"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nG. H. Golub and C. F. Van Loan, Matrix Computations,\nBaltimore, MD, Johns Hopkins University Press, 1985, pg. 15",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "References"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "from numpy import linalg as LA"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.arange(9) - 4"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([-4, -3, -2, ...,  2,  3,  4])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "b = a.reshape((3, 3))"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "b"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([[-4, -3, -2],"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "       [-1,  0,  1],"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "       [ 2,  3,  4]])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.745966692414834"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.745966692414834"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, 'fro')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.745966692414834"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, we.inf)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "4.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, we.inf)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "9.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, -we.inf)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "0.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, -we.inf)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "2.0"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, 1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "20.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, 1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, -1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "-4.6566128774142013e-010"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, -1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "6.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, 2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.745966692414834"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, 2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "7.3484692283495345"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, -2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "0.0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(b, -2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "1.8570331885190563e-016 # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, 3)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "5.8480354764257312 # may vary"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(a, -3)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "0.0"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Using the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " argument to compute vector norms:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "c = we.array([[ 1, 2, 3],"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": "...",
                "text": "[-1, 1, 4]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(c, axis=0)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([ 1.41421356,  2.23606798,  5.        ])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(c, axis=1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([ 3.74165739,  4.24264069])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(c, ord=1, axis=1)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([ 6.,  6.])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Using the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "axis"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " argument to compute matrix norms:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "m = we.arange(8).reshape(2,2,2)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(m, axis=(1,2))"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([  3.74165739,  11.22497216])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "LA.norm(m[0, :, :]), LA.norm(m[1, :, :])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "(3.7416573867739413, 11.224972160321824)"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
